### Step 5: Neighbors in Hexagonal Grid
In a hexagonal grid, neighbors of a cell depend on its position.
For a cell in ring k, its neighbors are:
- Two neighbors in the same ring (before and after along the spiral, if not at corner)
- Two neighbors in ring k-1 (inner ring)
- Two neighbors in ring k+1 (outer ring)
At corners of the ring, the pattern changes slightly (only one neighbor in same ring).

For number 2026, in ring 26, side 3, position 23 out of 26, it's not at the corner (corners are position 1 and 26 of the side), so it has:
- Previous number in spiral: 2025 (same ring, position 22 in side 3)
- Next number in spiral: 2027 (same ring, position 24 in side 3)
- Two inner neighbors in ring 25
- Two outer neighbors in ring 27

